The paper addresses the problem of clustering massive datasets, which is a common problem in data science and machine learning. The use of graph-based techniques and the mention of Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The mention of non-parametric methods and the comparison with other clustering algorithms suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of density-based methods and the mention of DBSCAN suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The mention of theoretical guarantees and the use of graph sketching suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the mention of no input parameter needed and the use of a new method suggest that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
